This virtual sitting of the ANC's 55th National Conference is unprecedented and unfortunate, but the President insists it is necessary. He has called for both discipline and patience from delegates to get through the agenda. #eNCA #DStv43  JOHANNESBURG - This virtual sitting of the ANC's 55th National Conference is unprecedented and unfortunate, but ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa insists it is necessary. He has called for both discipline and patience from delegates to get through the agenda. At the same time, Ramaphosa has acknowledged the party has often failed to implement its policies, leading to a breakdown in trust between it and the people. Watch the video above for more details.